9:1168:12:11:55:61:g_d0_f3:?:ABSTRACT
9:1169:11:12:55:61:g_d0_f2:?:Reconstruction of skull defects is regarded as an important surgical phase of recovery after traumatic brain injury. The dynamics 
9:1170:12:11:75:61:g_d0_f2:?:of cognitive functions after cranioplasty is of interest to researchers around the world, but this theme is not studied enough. 
9:1171:11:12:75:61:g_d0_f2:?:A signifi cant increase of patients with skull defects due to the aggressive surgical treatment of patients with severe traumatic 
9:1172:12:11:75:60:g_d0_f2:?:brain injury necessitates further study. In the emotional sphere of patients — depression is the most common complication after 
9:1173:11:12:75:61:g_d0_f2:?:traumatic brain injury (TBI). Severe depression after TBI worsens the quality of life and affects the recovery of interpersonal, 
9:1174:12:12:75:61:g_d0_f2:?:professional and social function of patients, as well as the results of further rehabilitation. The results of the studies emphasize 
9:1175:12:11:75:61:g_d0_f2:?:the importance of psychotherapeutic interventions to solve the problem of depression in the early period after TBI, which helps 
9:1176:11:12:75:61:g_d0_f2:?:to reduce the progression of depression in the fi rst year after the injury.
9:1177:12:0:55:61:g_d0_f3:?:Keywords: emotional and personal sphere, cognitive functions, cranioplasty.
